The paper focuses on optimization of interactive web pages, which involves decision-making and modeling of interactions between different components of the page. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the use of bandit methodology and hill-climbing for efficient exploration and selection of optimal content suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The optimization of search engine result pages and contextualization/personalization of layout selection suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY), respectively.
